11601 0U, // X

11610 0U, // XR
11611 0U, // XRK
11612 0U, // XSCH
11613 0U, // XY
11614 0U, // ZAP
11615 };
11616
11617 // Emit the opcode for the instruction.
11618 uint64_t Bits = 0;
11619 Bits |= (uint64_t)OpInfo0[MI->getOpcode()] << 0;
11620 Bits |= (uint64_t)OpInfo1[MI->getOpcode()] << 32;
11621 Bits |= (uint64_t)OpInfo2[MI->getOpcode()] << 48;
11622 return {AsmStrs+(Bits & 32767)-1, Bits};
11623
11624}

12188 // CU12, CU14, CU21, CU24, CUTFU, CUUTF, LCBB, LOCAsm, LOCFHAsm, LOCGAsm,...
12189 printU4ImmOperand(MI, 4, O);
12190 return;
12191 break;
12192 case 14:
12193 // DIDBR, DIEBR, LPTEA, MADBR, MADR, MAEBR, MAER, MAYHR, MAYLR, MAYR, MSD...
12194 printOperand(MI, 3, O);
12195 break;
12196 case 15:
12197 // InsnRIE, InsnRRF, InsnRRS, InsnRS, InsnRSE, InsnRSI, InsnRSY, InsnRXF,...
12198 O << ',';
12199 break;
12200 case 16:
12201 // LOCFHRAsm, LOCGHIAsm, LOCGRAsm, LOCHHIAsm, LOCHIAsm, LOCRAsm, STOCAsm,...
12202 printU4ImmOperand(MI, 3, O);
12203 return;
12204 break;
12205 case 17:
12206 // MAD, MADB, MAE, MAEB, MAY, MAYH, MAYL, MSD, MSDB, MSE, MSEB
12207 printBDXAddrOperand(MI, 3, O);
12208 return;
12209 break;
12210 case 18:
12211 // MY, MYH, MYL, SLDT, SLXT, SRDT, SRXT
12212 printBDXAddrOperand(MI, 2, O);
12213 return;
12214 break;
12215 case 19:
12216 // RISBG, RISBG32, RISBGN, RISBHG, RISBLG, RNSBG, ROSBG, RXSBG, VLRL, VPK...
12217 printU8ImmOperand(MI, 3, O);
12218 break;
12219 case 20:
12220 // SRP, VLEB
12221 printU4ImmOperand(MI, 5, O);
12222 return;
12223 break;
12224 case 21:
12225 // VCVD, VCVDG, VPSOP, VSRP
12226 printU8ImmOperand(MI, 2, O);
12227 O << ", ";
12228 break;
12229 case 22:
12230 // VFTCI, VFTCIDB, VFTCISB, WFTCIDB, WFTCISB, WFTCIXB
12231 printU12ImmOperand(MI, 2, O);
12232 break;
12233 case 23:
12234 // VLEBRF, VLEF
12235 printU2ImmOperand(MI, 5, O);
12236 return;
12237 break;
12238 case 24:
12239 // VLEBRG, VLEG
12240 printU1ImmOperand(MI, 5, O);
12241 return;
12242 break;
12243 case 25:
12244 // VLEBRH, VLEH
12245 printU3ImmOperand(MI, 5, O);
12246 return;
12247 break;
12248 case 26:
12249 // VLEIF
12250 printU2ImmOperand(MI, 3, O);
12251 return;
12252 break;
12253 case 27:
12254 // VLEIG
12255 printU1ImmOperand(MI, 3, O);
12256 return;
12257 break;
12258 case 28:
12259 // VLEIH
12260 printU3ImmOperand(MI, 3, O);
12261 return;
12262 break;
12263 case 29:
12264 // VREP, VREPB, VREPF, VREPG, VREPH
12265 printU16ImmOperand(MI, 2, O);
12266 break;
12267 case 30:
12268 // VSTEBRF, VSTEF
12269 printU2ImmOperand(MI, 4, O);
12270 return;
12271 break;
12272 case 31:
12273 // VSTEBRG, VSTEG
12274 printU1ImmOperand(MI, 4, O);
12275 return;
12276 break;
12277 case 32:
12278 // VSTEBRH, VSTEH
12279 printU3ImmOperand(MI, 4, O);
12280 return;
12281 break;
12282 }
12283
12284
12285 // Fragment 5 encoded into 4 bits for 12 unique commands.
12286 switch ((Bits >> 42) & 15) {
12287 default: llvm_unreachable("Invalid command number.");
12288 case 0:
12289 // ADTR, AGRK, AHHHR, AHHLR, ALGRK, ALHHHR, ALHHLR, ALRK, ARK, AXTR, BXH,...
12290 return;
12291 break;
12292 case 1:
12293 // ADTRA, AXTRA, CGRBAsm, CGRJAsm, CLGRBAsm, CLGRJAsm, CLRBAsm, CLRJAsm, ...
12294 O << ", ";
12295 break;
12296 case 2:
12297 // InsnRIE, InsnRSI
12298 printPCRelOperand(MI, Address, 3, O);
12299 return;
12300 break;
12301 case 3:
12302 // InsnRRF, InsnVRR
12303 printOperand(MI, 3, O);
12304 O << ',';
12305 printU4ImmOperand(MI, 4, O);
12306 break;
12307 case 4:
12308 // InsnRRS, VCVD, VCVDG
12309 printU4ImmOperand(MI, 3, O);
12310 break;
12311 case 5:
12312 // InsnRS, InsnRSE, InsnRSY
12313 printBDAddrOperand(MI, 3, O);
12314 return;
12315 break;
12316 case 6:
12317 // InsnRXF
12318 printBDXAddrOperand(MI, 3, O);
12319 return;
12320 break;
12321 case 7:
12322 // InsnSSF
12323 printOperand(MI, 5, O);
12324 return;
12325 break;
12326 case 8:
12327 // InsnVRI
12328 printU12ImmOperand(MI, 3, O);
12329 O << ',';
12330 printU4ImmOperand(MI, 4, O);
12331 O << ',';
12332 printU4ImmOperand(MI, 5, O);
12333 return;
12334 break;
12335 case 9:
12336 // InsnVRX
12337 printU4ImmOperand(MI, 5, O);
12338 return;
12339 break;
12340 case 10:
12341 // InsnVSI
12342 printU8ImmOperand(MI, 4, O);
12343 return;
12344 break;
12345 case 11:
12346 // VPSOP, VSRP
12347 printU8ImmOperand(MI, 3, O);
12348 O << ", ";
12349 printU4ImmOperand(MI, 4, O);
12350 return;
12351 break;
12352 }
12353
12354
12355 // Fragment 6 encoded into 4 bits for 11 unique commands.
12356 switch ((Bits >> 46) & 15) {
12357 default: llvm_unreachable("Invalid command number.");
12358 case 0:
12359 // ADTRA, AXTRA, CRDTE, DDTRA, DXTRA, IDTE, IPTE, MDTRA, MXTRA, SDTRA, SE...
12360 printU4ImmOperand(MI, 3, O);
12361 break;
12362 case 1:
12363 // CGRBAsm, CLGRBAsm, CLRBAsm, CRBAsm
12364 printBDAddrOperand(MI, 3, O);
12365 return;
12366 break;
12367 case 2:
12368 // CGRJAsm, CLGRJAsm, CLRJAsm, CRJAsm
12369 printPCRelOperand(MI, Address, 3, O);
12370 return;
12371 break;
12372 case 3:
12373 // DIDBR, DIEBR, LPTEA, QADTR, QAXTR, RRDTR, RRXTR, VERLL, VESL, VESRA, V...
12374 printU4ImmOperand(MI, 4, O);
12375 return;
12376 break;
12377 case 4:
12378 // InsnRRF, VCVD, VCVDG
12379 return;
12380 break;
12381 case 5:
12382 // InsnRRS, InsnVRR
12383 O << ',';
12384 break;
12385 case 6:
12386 // LMD, PLO
12387 printBDAddrOperand(MI, 4, O);
12388 return;
12389 break;
12390 case 7:
12391 // RISBG, RISBG32, RISBGN, RISBHG, RISBLG, RNSBG, ROSBG, RXSBG, VERIM, VE...
12392 printU8ImmOperand(MI, 4, O);
12393 break;
12394 case 8:
12395 // VAC, VACCC, VACCCQ, VACQ, VFMA, VFMADB, VFMASB, VFMS, VFMSDB, VFMSSB, ...
12396 printOperand(MI, 3, O);
12397 break;
12398 case 9:
12399 // VAP, VDP, VMP, VMSP, VRP, VSDP, VSLD, VSLDB, VSP, VSRD
12400 printU8ImmOperand(MI, 3, O);
12401 break;
12402 case 10:
12403 // VLVG
12404 printU4ImmOperand(MI, 5, O);
12405 return;
12406 break;
12407 }
12408
12409
12410 // Fragment 7 encoded into 2 bits for 4 unique commands.
12411 switch ((Bits >> 50) & 3) {
12412 default: llvm_unreachable("Invalid command number.");
12413 case 0:
12414 // ADTRA, AXTRA, CRDTE, DDTRA, DXTRA, IDTE, IPTE, MDTRA, MXTRA, SDTRA, SE...
12415 return;
12416 break;
12417 case 1:
12418 // InsnRRS
12419 printBDAddrOperand(MI, 4, O);
12420 return;
12421 break;
12422 case 2:
12423 // InsnVRR
12424 printU4ImmOperand(MI, 5, O);
12425 O << ',';
12426 printU4ImmOperand(MI, 6, O);
12427 return;
12428 break;
12429 case 3:
12430 // RISBG, RISBG32, RISBGN, RISBHG, RISBLG, RNSBG, ROSBG, RXSBG, VAC, VACC...
12431 O << ", ";
12432 break;
12433 }
12434
12435
12436 // Fragment 8 encoded into 2 bits for 3 unique commands.
12437 switch ((Bits >> 52) & 3) {
12438 default: llvm_unreachable("Invalid command number.");
12439 case 0:
12440 // RISBG, RISBG32, RISBGN, RISBHG, RISBLG, RNSBG, ROSBG, RXSBG
12441 printU6ImmOperand(MI, 5, O);
12442 return;
12443 break;
12444 case 1:
12445 // VAC, VACCC, VAP, VCDG, VCDLG, VCEQ, VCFPL, VCFPS, VCGD, VCH, VCHL, VCL...
12446 printU4ImmOperand(MI, 4, O);
12447 break;
12448 case 2:
12449 // VERIM
12450 printU4ImmOperand(MI, 5, O);
12451 return;
12452 break;
12453 }
12454
12455
12456 // Fragment 9 encoded into 1 bits for 2 unique commands.
12457 if ((Bits >> 54) & 1) {
12458 // VFCE, VFCH, VFCHE, VFMA, VFMAX, VFMIN, VFMS, VFNMA, VFNMS, VMSL, VSTRC...
12459 O << ", ";
12460 printU4ImmOperand(MI, 5, O);
12461 return;
12462 } else {
12463 // VAC, VACCC, VAP, VCDG, VCDLG, VCEQ, VCFPL, VCFPS, VCGD, VCH, VCHL, VCL...
12464 return;
12465 }
12466
12467}

13020#ifndef NDEBUG
13021 static struct SortCheck {
13022 SortCheck(ArrayRef<PatternsForOpcode> OpToPatterns) {
13023 assert(std::is_sorted(
13024 OpToPatterns.begin(), OpToPatterns.end(),
13025 [](const PatternsForOpcode &L, const PatternsForOpcode &R) {
13026 return L.Opcode < R.Opcode;
13027 }) &&
13028 "tablegen failed to sort opcode patterns");
13029 }
13030 } sortCheckVar(OpToPatterns);
13031#endif
13032
13033 AliasMatchingData M {
13034 makeArrayRef(OpToPatterns),
13035 makeArrayRef(Patterns),
13036 makeArrayRef(Conds),
13037 StringRef(AsmStrings, array_lengthof(AsmStrings)),
13038 nullptr,
13039 };
13040 const char *AsmString = matchAliasPatterns(MI, nullptr, M);
13041 if (!AsmString) return false;
13042
13043 unsigned I = 0;
13044 while (AsmString[I] != ' ' && AsmString[I] != '\t' &&
13045 AsmString[I] != '$' && AsmString[I] != '\0')
13046 ++I;
13047 OS << '\t' << StringRef(AsmString, I);
13048 if (AsmString[I] != '\0') {
13049 if (AsmString[I] == ' ' || AsmString[I] == '\t') {
13050 OS << '\t';
13051 ++I;
13052 }
13053 do {
13054 if (AsmString[I] == '$') {
13055 ++I;
13056 if (AsmString[I] == (char)0xff) {
13057 ++I;
13058 int OpIdx = AsmString[I++] - 1;
13059 int PrintMethodIdx = AsmString[I++] - 1;
13060 printCustomAliasOperand(MI, Address, OpIdx, PrintMethodIdx, OS);
13061 } else
13062 printOperand(MI, unsigned(AsmString[I++]) - 1, OS);
13063 } else {
13064 OS << AsmString[I++];
13065 }
13066 } while (AsmString[I] != '\0');
13067 }
13068
13069 return true;
13070}
13071
13072void SystemZInstPrinter::printCustomAliasOperand(
13073 const MCInst *MI, uint64_t Address, unsigned OpIdx,
13074 unsigned PrintMethodIdx,
13075 raw_ostream &OS) {
13076 switch (PrintMethodIdx) {
13077 default:
13078 llvm_unreachable("Unknown PrintMethod kind");
13079 break;
13080 case 0:
13081 printU4ImmOperand(MI, OpIdx, OS);
13082 break;
13083 }
13084}
